Routing network traffic in Azure VNets is essential for controlling how data flows between resources.

For example, a company may route all outbound traffic through a firewall appliance for inspection.

A real-life use case is enterprise security where all internet-bound traffic is inspected before leaving the network.

Another example is directing traffic between subnets using custom routes for performance optimization.

Organizations also use routing to send traffic through VPN gateways for secure communication with on-premises systems.

These routing strategies ensure secure, efficient, and controlled network communication.
